list.abstract: graduate（英[ˈɡrædʒuət , ˈɡrædʒueɪt]，美[ˈɡrædʒuət , ˈɡrædʒueɪt]），英语单词，作名词用，为毕业生。作动词用，为获得学位；完成培训；从高中毕业。短语搭配有graduate from（毕业于；毕业自），例句为“Meiyu will graduate in June this year.（梅雨将于今年6月毕业。）” graduate不及物动词类近义词有shadow、to finish school，名词类近义词有postgraduate、advanced student，形容词类近义词有school-leaving，形容词形式为graduated、graded、gradational。graduate study的意思为研究生学习；研究生研究。graduate school的意思为研究生院。

yingyinNormal.en: You thought the opposite of "stupid loser" was "community college graduate"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你觉得"很傻很衰"的反义词是"社区大学毕业生"？

yingyinNormal.en: Phil and I have prepared something very special for our brilliant graduate, Alex. Okay, you ready?
yingyinNormal.zh: 菲尔和我给我们聪明的毕业生艾丽克斯准备了一个特别的贺礼。你准备好了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: A 25-year-old Harvard Law graduate took South Carolina State Senate District Fourteen by storm. His name was Francis J. Underwood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 25岁的哈佛法学院毕业生席卷了南卡罗莱纳州州参议院第14区，他的名字是弗兰西斯·J·安德伍德。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm even prouder to share a fundamental truth that you might not have learned, even as graduate of Harvard, unless you studied the ancient Greek role with professor Nagy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 同时，我要更自豪地分享一件事，尽管你们是哈佛毕业生，可能也不知道这个，除非你攻读的是纳吉教授的古希腊角色。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, because I had been a football star and war hero and national celebrity and a shrimping boat captain and a college graduate, the city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama, decided to get together and offered me a fine job.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在因为我成了足球明星和战争英雄，以及全国知名的人物和捕虾船的船长，以及大学毕业生，亚拉巴马州绿茵镇的父老乡亲，决定给我一个好工作。

yingyinNormal.en: Got myself a Mr. Sam Witwicky, recent college graduate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来了一个山姆威特维奇先生，刚毕业。

yingyinNormal.en: So as you graduate today, I want to put some pressure on you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在你们毕业的今天，我希望给你们一些压力。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: Howard. I appreciate the gesture, but this is a graduate-level physics class.
yingyinNormal.zh: 霍华德，感谢你的提议，但这是研究生阶段的物理课程。

yingyinNormal.en: Graduate school should probably do a better job of screening those people out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 学校毕业后可以找个比大多数人做得都好的工作。

yingyinNormal.en: And I made my company promise that I can't be transferred again until you graduate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要我的公司答应在你毕业前我不会再调动了。

yingyinNormal.en: By receiving their badges, the following explorers will graduate to Senior Explorers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在颁发徽章，以下探险者将升级为高级探险者。

yingyinNormal.en: But if we're all going to die the moment we graduate, isn't it what we do before that counts?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但如果我们在毕业的那一刻死去，难道不是在毕业前经历的一切最重要吗?

yingyinNormal.en: Looking out at your fresh young faces, I remember when I too was deciding my academic future as a lowly graduate student.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看见你们朝气蓬勃的脸庞，我回想起了我决定步入学术道路的那一刻，那时我还是个卑微的研究生。

yingyinNormal.en: Robbie Feinberg, the pinhead, took five years to finish high school. Alden Kupferberg, the Sea Otter, didn't even graduate.
yingyinNormal.zh: Robbie Feinberg "没头脑"花了5年才读完了高中，Alden Kupferberg "海獭"连高中都没毕业。

yingyinNormal.en: As mayor of Zootopia, I am proud to announce that my mammal inclusion initiative, has produced its first police academy graduate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作为动物城的市长，我很荣幸地宣布，哺乳动物选拔行动的第一批警校学员已经毕业了。

yingyinNormal.en: Only 211. Don't worry. In deference to you, I kept them all at a high school graduate reading level. Thanks, pal. You got it, buddy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 区区211个，别担心 为了照顾你，这份高中毕业就能读懂，还得谢你，哥们儿。客气啥...姐们儿。

yingyinNormal.en: A colleague of mine did her graduate thesis on the fungus that grows on improperly sterilized manicure implements. Well don't tell me that's not "girl talk".
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的一个同事的毕业论文就写的是消毒不当的美甲工具上滋生的霉菌，别说这不是女生话题。

yingyinNormal.en: At Harvard's commencement tomorrow as your dean described, each school is gonna stand up and graduate together, the college, the law school, the med school and so on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们院长也讲了，在明天的哈佛毕业典礼上，每个学院都要起立并一同毕业。本科部、法学院、医学院等等。

examination_example.sentence: The job security that the US economy once offered to high school <highlight>graduates</highlight> has largely evaporated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国经济曾经为高中毕业生提供的工作保障已经基本消失。

examination_example.sentence: David Graddol concludes that monoglot English <highlight>graduates</highlight> face a bleak economic future.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大卫·葛拉多尔的结论是，只会说一门英语的毕业生面临着黯淡的经济前景。

examination_example.sentence: These are the kind of workers that countries like Britain, Canada and Australia try to attract by using immigration rules that privilege college <highlight>graduates</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence_trans: 你的一位外国朋友最近大学毕业，打算在中国找工作。

examination_example.sentence: One survey from Accenture found that 88 percent of <highlight>graduating</highlight> seniors this year chose their major with a job in mind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 埃森哲咨询公司一项调查发现，今年毕业的大四学生中，88%的人选择专业时都考虑到了工作。

examination_example.sentence: He found a dream job after <highlight>graduating</highlight> from college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大学毕业后他找到了一份理想的工作。

sense_info_list.en: a person who has a first degree from a university or college

examination_example.sentence: But now most colleges, save for many selective campuses, allow all undergraduates, and even <highlight>graduate</highlight> students, to get their low grades forgiven.

examination_example.sentence: There's always a constant fear of falling behind everyone else , whether that be toward <highlight>graduate</highlight> school, medical school or a lucrative career.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们总是害怕落后于其他人，无论是上研究生院、医学院还是获得一份有利可图的职业。

examination_example.sentence: The scores were then used in conjunction with an applicant's score on the <highlight>Graduate</highlight> Management Admission Test, or GMAT.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些分数随后与申请人的研究生管理科学入学考试（GMAT）分数一起使用。
